Kohane: (...! That was a tricky transition, but they were in perfect unison!)
Audience: “They're totally in sync! You can tell that they're sisters!”
Audience: “Hey, being sisters isn't what makes them great. Elena and Rebecca are just on another level entirely.”
Akito: They're good...
Toya: Yes. We've seen quite a number of street artists since coming over to the United States. But they're...
Toya: They're something special.
Elena: “Whew, I had a blast! Thanks for listening, everyone!”
Audience: “Wait, don't tell us that you're done!”
Audience: “We wanna hear more!”
Elena: “Haha. Sorry, you guys!”
Elena: “We have plans after this. I promised Becky that we'd only sing for a little bit, so we have to call things here for today!”
Audience: “Please! We beg you!”
Elena: “Hmm... I don't know, guys...”
Kohane: (Did we just make eye contact?)
Elena: “I've got a great idea...! Hey, hey, Becky! Look!”
Kohane: (Wh-What's going on? Those two seem really interested in me for some reason...)
Rebecca: “Oh, that is a nice idea... That should let us end things on a high note.”
Rebecca: “But only if she says yes.”
Elena: “Okay! Then, I'll try asking her!”
Elena: “Hey, you there!”
Kohane: “Huh? Me...?”
Elena: “Yeah, you! You're the girl who was singing earlier this morning, yeah?”
Elena: “You wanna sing with us?”
An: Did she just invite Kohane to sing with them?
Toya: Yes...
Kohane: U-Uhh...
Elena: S-Sorry, I didn't mean to startle you! My name's Elena!
An: Wait, you speak Japanese...?
Elena: The way you sang sent a jolt through me. I've been wanting to sing with you all day!
Elena: Becky... Oh, umm... My little sister also wants to sing with you. So, what do you say?
Kohane: Umm...
Kohane: (What do I do?)
Audience: “Huh? Is she gonna sing with them?”
Audience: “I've never seen her before...”
Kohane: (Wait, everyone's looking at me now!)
Kohane: (I was honestly a little startled at first, but...)
Elena & Rebecca: ♪————! ♪————————!
Kohane: (I was really drawn to their singing style. It was so powerful, but so free and fun too.)
Kohane: (How would it feel to sing alongside that?)
Kohane: Okay!
Kohane: Umm... Sorry, you guys. Would you mind waiting here for a minute?
An: Okay! Go have fun!
Elena: Hehe. Then, let's go!
Toya: There she goes.
Akito: Yeah... What are they gonna sing?
An: You've got this, Kohane!
Rebecca: Thanks for agreeing to do this! I'm Rebecca. Call me Becky!
Kohane: Nice to meet you! My name is Kohane Azusawa.
Kohane: (Becky's Japanese is really good too...)
Rebecca: Kohane? Got it! We can't sing the same song again, so...
Rebecca: Why don't we take turns singing to this beat?
Kohane: Okay, that sounds good!
Elena: Alright, then... Let's have a good time, girls♪
